text: Public health officials in Contra Costa County reported five additional deaths due to the coronavirus Wednesday. The county has reported 23 of its 67 total deaths in the last nine days. https://t.co/GrgJwt3Zvc

Thumbing through baseball’s 100-plus page protocol for the abbreviated 2020 season is difficult enough.

Imagine being the person responsible for implementing all of it in the midst of a pandemic.

text: California's ready to speed up the enforcement of AB5 with a lawsuit, which would compel Uber and Lyft to reclassify their drivers as employees within the next few weeks. The suit is asking for a hearing on July 23. https://t.co/3zKbcQm9aZ
